The premiere of the sixth season of Africa’s biggest reality show, Big Brother Naija, will feature a double launch show on Saturday and Sunday. According to a statement on Tuesday, both shows will air from 7pm on DStv channel 198 and GOtv channel 29, as well as Africa Magic Showcase, Africa Magic Urban and Africa Magic Family. The Chief Executive Officer of MultiChoice Nigeria, John Ugbe quoted in the statement said, “With each season of BBNaija we task ourselves with delivering great content that will take the excitement a notch higher and meet the entertainment needs of our customers.” The reality TV show will run for 10 weeks and its winner will be given the prize of N90 million. “The 10-week long reality TV show will follow the lives of strangers as they interact and compete with each other to win the grand prize of N90m worth of prizes, which is the biggest in reality TV show reward on the continent,” the statement read partly. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com